[all talking at once]

01:27.450 --> 01:29.816
- [sniffles]
- Hey.

01:29.817 --> 01:33.688
Maybe you're more tired
than you think, sweetie, hm?

01:33.691 --> 01:36.439
- No, no, it's, um--

01:36.442 --> 01:41.304
I love the New York
Symphony, I do.

01:41.305 --> 01:43.128
It's our home.

01:43.129 --> 01:45.367
I don't want anything bad
to happen to it.

01:45.370 --> 01:46.841
- Of course not.

01:46.843 --> 01:49.847
No, no, no, no, no,
we'll do everything, right?

01:49.849 --> 01:54.329
Everything we need to do
to keep the orchestra going.

01:54.331 --> 01:55.769
Look at that.

01:55.771 --> 01:57.593
You know, it's nice
that we're talking again.

01:57.594 --> 02:00.727
I kind of missed you,
eh, Sharon?

02:00.730 --> 02:02.615
- Yes, it seems like
a million years ago

02:02.617 --> 02:04.984
since we were sucking face in
the wings of the symphony hall.

02:04.986 --> 02:08.216
- Sucking face, that's just
such a horrible way to say it.

02:08.217 --> 02:10.745
I mean, what, am I a fish
with no feelings, or what?

02:10.747 --> 02:12.664
Why do you talk
to me like that?

02:12.667 --> 02:14.103
- Edward's this way.

02:14.105 --> 02:16.183
- So how long have you been
working with the Biben?

02:16.186 --> 02:18.039
- The Biben?
- Mm.

02:18.042 --> 02:19.480
- Longer than I worked for you.

02:19.483 --> 02:21.848
He's an incredible man.
- Yeah, incredible.

02:21.849 --> 02:23.161
Incredible at what?

02:23.163 --> 02:25.111
- He's incredible
at being incredible.

02:25.114 --> 02:26.711
- Say it again.
Say it again into my eyes.

02:26.713 --> 02:28.025
Go on.

02:28.026 --> 02:29.944
- He's incredible
at being incredible.

02:29.947 --> 02:31.512
- Where's Mr. Incredible?
Where is he?

02:31.514 --> 02:33.881
Where is he?

